---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="signs-page">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gray-800 text-white py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold">10 Signs Your Las Vegas Home Needs a New Electrical Panel</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Your electrical panel works silently in the background, but when it fails, it gives clear warning signs. Here's what to look for.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content Area -->
    <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-12">
          
          <!-- Article Content (Left Column) -->
          <article class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-12">
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
              <p>Your electrical panel is the heart of your home's power system. But in many older Las Vegas homes, these panels are struggling to keep up with modern demands. Ignoring the warning signs of an overloaded or failing panel can lead to appliance damage, power outages, and even electrical fires. Here are the top 10 signs it's time to call a professional.</p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Signs Section -->
            <div>
              <div class="space-y-8">
                <!-- Sign 1 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">1</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">Your Circuit Breakers Keep Tripping</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">A breaker tripping occasionally is normal. But if it happens frequently, it's a major red flag. It means your panel is consistently overloaded and can't handle the amount of electricity your home is trying to draw.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 2 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">2</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">Flickering or Dimming Lights</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">If your lights dim every time the AC kicks on or you use the microwave, it indicates an outdated or overloaded panel that can't provide consistent power to all circuits simultaneously.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 3 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">3</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">You Still Have a Fuse Box</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">If your home has a fuse box instead of a modern circuit breaker panel, it's time for an immediate upgrade. Fuse boxes are obsolete technology, lack critical safety features, and are often uninsurable.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 4 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">4</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">A Burning Smell or Scorch Marks</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">Any smell of burning plastic or visible scorch marks around the panel or outlets is a sign of a dangerous electrical fault. Call a licensed electrician immediately.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 5 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">5</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">Your Panel is a Federal Pacific or Zinsco Brand</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">These brands are notorious for having design flaws that cause their breakers to fail to trip, creating a major fire hazard. We specialize in replacing these dangerous panels.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 6 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">6</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">You're Planning a Major Renovation</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">Adding a room, a new kitchen, or a pool will significantly increase your power needs. An upgrade is often required by Clark County code for such projects.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 7 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">7</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">You're Installing an EV Charger or Hot Tub</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">These high-draw appliances require dedicated, high-amperage circuits that most older 100-amp or 150-amp panels simply cannot support safely.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 8 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">8</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">You Rely on Extension Cords</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">If you have power strips and extension cords in every room, it's a sign your home's electrical system wasn't designed for your lifestyle. A new panel allows for the safe addition of more outlets.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 9 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">9</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">Your Home is Over 25 Years Old</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">Electrical panels aren't designed to last forever. If your panel is original to a home built more than 25-30 years ago, it's wise to have it inspected and likely replaced before problems begin.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Sign 10 -->
                <div class="flex items-start mb-8">
                  <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-accent font-extrabold text-4xl w-12 text-center mr-2">10</div>
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">Your Homeowner's Insurance Requires It</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">Many insurance companies will raise premiums or refuse to renew policies for homes with outdated panels or fuse boxes due to the high risk of fire.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Conclusion -->
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none pt-8">
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Don't Ignore the Warning Signs</h2>
              <p>If any of these signs sound familiar, don't wait for a small problem to become a dangerous one. A modern, professional <a href="/" class="text-accent font-semibold hover:underline">electrical panel upgrade</a> is the best way to ensure your home is safe and ready for the future. It's a smart investment that protects your family and your property. To understand the investment better, you can review our guide on the <a href="/cost-of-panel-upgrade-las-vegas" class="text-accent font-semibold hover:underline">cost of a panel upgrade in Las Vegas</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </article>
          
          <!-- Sidebar (Right Column) -->
          <aside class="lg:col-span-1 mt-12 lg:mt-0">
            <div class="sticky top-24 space-y-8" id="stickyQuote">
              <div class="bg-orange-400 p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Seeing Any of These Signs?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">Don't risk it. Schedule a free, no-obligation inspection and estimate with our licensed Las Vegas electricians.</p>
                <a href="/company/company/contact-us/" class="w-full text-center bg-orange-500 text-black font-bold py-3 px-5 rounded-full hover:bg-orange-300 transition-colors duration-300 inline-block text-lg">Schedule Free Inspection</a>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 text-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Our Core Services</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                  <li><a href="/#services" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">✓ 200 Amp Panel Upgrades</a></li>
                  <li><a href="/#services" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">✓ Fuse Box Conversions</a></li>
                  <li><a href="/#services" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">✓ Circuit Breaker Replacement</a></li>
                  <li><a href="/#services" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">✓ Emergency Repairs</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 1023px) {
    #stickyQuote {
      position: relative !important;
      top: 0 !important;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Handle sticky positioning to work with the sticky header
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    const header = document.getElementById("site-header");
    const stickyQuote = document.getElementById("stickyQuote");
    
    if (header && stickyQuote) {
      function adjustStickyTop() {
        // When header is fixed, add its height as top margin for the sticky container
        const headerIsFixed = window.getComputedStyle(header).position === "fixed";
        if (headerIsFixed) {
          stickyQuote.style.top = `${header.offsetHeight + 24}px`; // Add some extra padding
        } else {
          stickyQuote.style.top = "24px";
        }
      }
      
      // Run on scroll and on load
      window.addEventListener("scroll", adjustStickyTop);
      adjustStickyTop();
    }
  });
</script>
